cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.SOC, cs.HC, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the problem of automatically generating social networks by analyzing smartphone usage and interaction data. The paper proposes algorithms based on recent findings from social network research. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other likely sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Engineering), cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper deals with analyzing and assessing smartphone usage data.
